{
  "texts": [
    "This methodology capitalizes on preexisting language models by adapting them to a designated NER task by incorporating a specifically annotated corpus.",
    "This process enhances the model's performance in a specialized context, optimizing its proficiency in accurately identifying and categorizing named entities within the designated task domain.",
    "• In-context learning is a method that commonly integrates few-shot demonstrations or prompts during the training process to guide the behavior of the model for a specific task [16].",
    "This approach uses recent advances in Generative Pretrained Transformers (GPT) to address NER tasks, representing a pioneering paradigm, particularly in the intricate realm of processing and structuring complex healthcare data.",
    "In-context learning becomes especially relevant when applied to Spanish EHRs, where linguistic nuances pose unique challenges."
  ]
}